Unlimited plates, $0.25 mimosas, $6 crushes (regularly $9).  Each plate is around $6-8 so the bottomless is probably the way to go.  In terms of food, everything I had was good. The French toast, the chickpea hash, and gyro hash browns were among the favorites!!

This place has been solid for me in the past. But my last experience was horrible.  There was a cockroach running wild in the dining room. Two bus boys walked past it before I saw the manager, and was able to flag him down. Then, he killed it. He apologized and then told me that “they often come in when we leave the doors open”. The simple solution to not having cockroaches in your restaurant is to keep the doors closed, rather than wide open. The doors were closed when I came in for lunch, which means that roach was in there for at least a couple of hours. This should never happen in an eating establishment.  I’m a vegetarian and Cava Mezze has always been good for vegetarian options. However, when I went in last they hesitated to let me sub in a veggie dish for a meat/fish option on the “Mezze Mania” lunch menu. My server let me know it’s not possible outside getting a salad because “veggies cost more than meat”. Unless this restaurant is using the cheapest meat and fish they can find, that’s not possible. There is no way the Street Corn or Brussels Sprouts cost more than the gyro meatballs or shrimp. This is all ignoring the fact that Cava Mezze has never been tough on substitutions for vegetarians in the past. Never.  Sorry folks, this popular eastern market establishment is going down. Roaches that are dismissed as regular guests because the doors are left open. And a bad substitution policy backed by faulty economics. Used to love ya, now I can’t go back

I was so happy that this restaurant is featured on Seated so I decided to book immediately. We ordered the speciality, a cheese set on forest your table, and while the viewing of it was gorgeous, the dish itself was perfectly fine. It may be more pleasing alongside a meat, as it’s quite a bit of cheese that could use another distinct flavor to compliment it. We also ordered the roasted cauliflower, which I truly enjoyed. The sauce had a unique tangy flavor that then left an unexpected kick in your mouth after each bite. My friend ordered the risotto with scallops, which she really enjoyed. We tried 4 drinks on the cocktail menu. The sangria, cucumber, and berry drinks were all true to the description and tasty. We considered ordering dessert, but there were only three options which didn’t appeal to us at the moment. The two women who greeted us were incredibly friendly and offered thoughtful suggestions for bars for us to try following our meal. Our server himself was nice as well. Atmosphere is modern, trendy, and attracts a wide crowd from families to dates to singles. We didn’t feel pressured to leave and the atmosphere allowed for comfortable conversation. Overall, a good experience and I think exploring other menu items would be worth a second trip, plus another round of those awesome Amazon rewards thanks to Seated!
